 Triage Ransomware Infection & Initial Compromise
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Analyze ransomware artifacts and identify attack patterns
Investigate system logs to trace infection vectors
Extract and document indicators of compromise (IOCs)
Perform forensic triage on a compromised Linux system
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line knowledge
Understanding of file systems and log structures
Familiarity with network concepts and protocols
Knowledge of common ransomware attack vectors
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides Linux-based cloud machines for this lab. Simply click Start Lab to access your dedicated environment. The provided Linux machine is bare metal with no pre-installed tools, so you will install all required tools during the lab exercises.

Task 1: Set Up Forensic Environment and Create Simulated Ransomware Scenario
Subtask 1.1: Install Required Tools
# Update system packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install forensic and analysis tools
sudo apt install -y volatility3 sleuthkit autopsy binwalk hexdump tree file strings grep awk sed

# Install additional utilities
sudo apt install -y python3-pip curl wget unzip
pip3 install yara-python
Subtask 1.2: Create Simulated Ransomware Environment
# Create directory structure for simulation
mkdir -p ~/ransomware_lab/{evidence,analysis,logs,tools}
cd ~/ransomware_lab

# Create sample files that will be "encrypted"
mkdir -p evidence/user_data/{documents,pictures,videos}
echo "Important business document" > evidence/user_data/documents/contract.txt
echo "Financial records 2024" > evidence/user_data/documents/finances.xlsx
echo "Family photo metadata" > evidence/user_data/pictures/vacation.jpg
echo "Project presentation" > evidence/user_data/documents/presentation.pptx

# Simulate ransomware encryption by renaming files
for file in evidence/user_data/documents/* evidence/user_data/pictures/*; do
    mv "$file" "$file.locked"
done

# Create ransomware note
cat > evidence/user_data/README_DECRYPT.txt << 'EOF'
YOUR FILES HAVE BEEN ENCRYPTED!

All your important files have been encrypted with military-grade encryption.
To recover your files, you must pay 0.5 Bitcoin to: 1A2B3C4D5E6F7G8H9I0J

Contact: decrypt@darkweb.onion
Deadline: 72 hours

Do not attempt to decrypt files yourself or use third-party software.
This will result in permanent data loss.
EOF
Subtask 1.3: Generate System Artifacts
# Create fake system logs showing infection timeline
sudo mkdir -p /var/log/ransomware_sim

# Simulate auth log entries
cat > /tmp/auth_entries << 'EOF'
Dec 15 14:23:45 victim-pc sshd[1234]: Failed password for admin from 192.168.1.100 port 22 ssh2
Dec 15 14:24:12 victim-pc sshd[1235]: Accepted password for admin from 192.168.1.100 port 22 ssh2
Dec 15 14:25:33 victim-pc sudo: admin : TTY=pts/0 ; PWD=/home/admin ; USER=root ; COMMAND=/bin/bash
EOF

# Simulate syslog entries showing suspicious activity
cat > /tmp/syslog_entries << 'EOF'
Dec 15 14:26:15 victim-pc kernel: [12345.678] TCP: request_sock_TCP: Possible SYN flooding on port 445
Dec 15 14:27:22 victim-pc systemd[1]: Started malicious-service.service
Dec 15 14:28:45 victim-pc cron[5678]: (root) CMD (/tmp/.hidden/encrypt.sh)
Dec 15 14:30:12 victim-pc NetworkManager[910]: <warn> connection 'Wired connection 1' failed: large data transfer detected
EOF

# Copy to analysis directory
cp /tmp/auth_entries ~/ransomware_lab/logs/
cp /tmp/syslog_entries ~/ransomware_lab/logs/
Task 2: Analyze Ransomware Artifacts
Subtask 2.1: Examine File System Changes
cd ~/ransomware_lab

# Analyze file extensions and patterns
echo "=== ENCRYPTED FILES ANALYSIS ==="
find evidence/ -name "*.locked" -type f | head -10

# Check file signatures of encrypted files
echo -e "\n=== FILE SIGNATURE ANALYSIS ==="
for file in $(find evidence/ -name "*.locked" | head -3); do
    echo "File: $file"
    hexdump -C "$file" | head -2
    echo "---"
done

# Examine ransomware note
echo -e "\n=== RANSOMWARE NOTE ANALYSIS ==="
cat evidence/user_data/README_DECRYPT.txt
Subtask 2.2: Extract IOCs from Ransomware Note
# Extract potential IOCs
echo "=== EXTRACTED IOCs ==="
echo "Bitcoin Address:" 
grep -o '1[A-Za-z0-9]*' evidence/user_data/README_DECRYPT.txt

echo -e "\nEmail/Contact:"
grep -o '[a-zA-Z0-9]*@[a-zA-Z0-9]*\.[a-zA-Z]*' evidence/user_data/README_DECRYPT.txt

echo -e "\nFile Extension:"
find evidence/ -name "*.locked" | head -1 | grep -o '\.locked$'

# Create IOC report
cat > analysis/ioc_report.txt << 'EOF'
INDICATORS OF COMPROMISE (IOCs)
===============================

File Indicators:
- Extension: .locked
- Ransom Note: README_DECRYPT.txt
