Conclusion
You have successfully completed a comprehensive ransomware triage investigation. Through this lab, you:

Analyzed ransomware artifacts including encrypted files, ransom notes, and system modifications
Investigated infection vectors by examining authentication and system logs to trace the attack timeline
Identified critical IOCs including file signatures, network indicators, and behavioral patterns
Created detection rules and mitigation strategies to prevent future incidents
This hands-on experience demonstrates real-world incident response procedures used by cybersecurity professionals to investigate ransomware attacks. The skills developed here are essential for threat hunting, digital forensics, and security operations center (SOC) roles. Understanding how to quickly triage and analyze ransomware infections is crucial for minimizing damage and implementing effective recovery strategies in enterprise environments.
